<html
    xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
    xml:lang="en"
    lang="en"
    metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
    i18n:domain="launchpad">

<head>
    <title metal:fill-slot="title">Overview of Distributions in
    Soyuz</title>
    <!-- Plone style sheet -->
    <style type="text/css" media="screen">@import url(plone.css);</style>
    <!-- Soyuz style sheet -->
    <style type="text/css" media="screen">@import url(soyuz.css);</style>
</head>

<body>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">

    <h1>Distribution Management: All Distributions</h1>

    
        <p>This page shows all distributions that are
        registered in the Launchpad. Note that some of these
        distributions are "read-only", we monitor those distributions and
        present package information for them in Soyuz, but they cannot be
        altered or managed in Soyuz. The Soyuz representations of those
        distributions might be out of date.</p>

    <table width="100%" class="listing rowNavigation">
        <tr>
            <th>Name</th>
            <th>Title</th>
        </tr>
        <tr tal:repeat="distribution context"
            tal:attributes="onclick
                string:window.location='/soyuz/distros/${distribution/name}'">
            <td>
                <a tal:content="distribution/name" 
	               tal:attributes="href
                       distribution/name">
	               distribution name
	            </a>
                <span tal:condition="python: distribution.name in ['redhat', 'debian', 'gentoo']">
                    *
                </span>
            </td>
            <td tal:content="distribution/title">
                distribution title
            </td>
        </tr>
    </table>    

    <div style="float: right;">
        * read-only distribution. (<span tal:replace="view/count" />
        distributions in total)
    </div>

    <p><img src="/++resource++add.gif"> <a href="+add">Add
    New Distribution</a></p>

</div>

</body>
</html>
